WEBVTT

00:07.000 --> 00:09.767
[ Fire crackling ]

00:09.767 --> 00:13.033
[ Off-key "Frère Jacques"
playing ]

00:13.033 --> 00:15.600
[ Footsteps approaching ]

00:19.633 --> 00:22.300
[ Metal clanks, scrapes ]

00:35.733 --> 00:38.167
[ Music continues ]

00:49.867 --> 00:52.467
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:08.133 --> 01:09.200
[ Grunts ]

01:09.200 --> 01:12.067
[ Theme music plays ]

01:31.233 --> 01:33.667
[ Music continues ]

02:11.167 --> 02:13.767
HARRY: It is most gratifying,
I must say,

02:13.767 --> 02:16.500
to see such
an impressive turnout.

02:17.600 --> 02:18.800
I'm sure most of you are here

02:18.800 --> 02:21.833
to make sure I don't change
my mind.

02:21.833 --> 02:24.067
Almost rid of the old witch.

02:24.067 --> 02:26.733
[ Laughter ]

02:26.733 --> 02:29.200
Those of you that will be happy
to see the back of me,

02:29.200 --> 02:33.200
it'll probably be because I was
hard on you over the years.

02:34.267 --> 02:38.067
I want you to know
that I was hard on you

02:38.067 --> 02:40.733
because you are
arrogant little shits.

02:40.733 --> 02:42.867
[ Laughter ]

02:43.433 --> 02:46.133
I see your type year after year.

02:46.133 --> 02:50.067
You take this course because
you think, "Oh, it's easy.

02:50.067 --> 02:51.767
Only books."

02:53.333 --> 02:55.267
To you...

02:56.333 --> 03:01.767
...I say that you are a shameful
waste of skin and air.

03:01.767 --> 03:04.067
[ Laughter ]

03:05.367 --> 03:08.067
Had you paid attention
these last three years,

03:08.067 --> 03:10.200
you would know
that the mathematicians

03:10.200 --> 03:13.300
and scientists tell us
how we are here.

03:13.867 --> 03:19.300
Historians can tell us when, but
only literature can tell us why.

03:24.633 --> 03:27.567
Those of you
who did pay attention...

03:29.467 --> 03:34.500
...I just want to say
thank you...

03:36.133 --> 03:38.633
...from the bottom of my heart.

03:41.533 --> 03:43.400
You've made this all worthwhile.

03:43.400 --> 03:45.100
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

03:48.600 --> 03:52.067
And now I have a little surprise
for all of you.

03:56.067 --> 03:58.067
[ Door closes ]

04:00.400 --> 04:03.333
[ Students murmuring ]

04:03.333 --> 04:05.167
-Hip-hip...
-GROUP: Hooray!

04:05.167 --> 04:06.433
Hip-hip-hip...

04:06.433 --> 04:07.567
Hooray!

04:07.567 --> 04:09.233
Hip-hip-hip...

04:09.233 --> 04:12.067
-Hooray!
-Whoo-hoo!

04:12.067 --> 04:14.067
[ Up-tempo music playing ]

04:14.067 --> 04:15.733
Ah!

04:15.733 --> 04:18.833
You're making a huge mistake.

04:18.833 --> 04:21.467
Don't be ridiculous.
I never make mistakes.

04:21.467 --> 04:25.333
What are you gonna do
with yourself in retirement?

04:25.333 --> 04:26.600
I don't know.

04:26.600 --> 04:29.067
All the things
I never had time for.

04:29.067 --> 04:31.233
Sort out the attic.

04:31.233 --> 04:33.633
Do some gardening.
[ Chuckles ]

04:34.167 --> 04:35.767
Write that great novel.

04:35.767 --> 04:38.800
Oh! I may even spend some time
with my granddaughter.

04:38.800 --> 04:40.467
You don't like children.

04:40.467 --> 04:44.267
Well, she'll be interesting
in a year or two, hopefully.

04:44.267 --> 04:46.233
Unless she takes after
her mother.

04:46.233 --> 04:47.867
Did you invite Charlie tonight?

04:47.867 --> 04:49.433
God, no!

04:49.433 --> 04:51.200
I'm planning
on getting shit-faced

04:51.200 --> 04:54.367
and snogging
the new archaeology professor.

04:55.400 --> 04:57.167
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:58.633 --> 05:01.600
Sorensen.
History prof.

05:01.600 --> 05:04.533
Made almost the same speech
at his retirement.

05:04.533 --> 05:07.433
That he wanted to snog
the new archaeology professor?

05:07.433 --> 05:09.067
No.

05:09.067 --> 05:12.400
I think he wanted to spend
more time caravanning

05:12.400 --> 05:14.667
or something else
similarly wretched.

05:14.667 --> 05:16.800
Yeah, I remember.
So...

05:16.800 --> 05:19.633
Six months later -- dead.

05:20.233 --> 05:23.867
And this, Graham, is why you're
not invited to more parties.

05:25.067 --> 05:26.367
To Harry.

05:26.367 --> 05:29.233
GROUP:
To Harry!

05:29.233 --> 05:31.633
[ Music continues ]

05:31.633 --> 05:34.733
NEWSCASTER: Concerns are growing
for Kayleigh Connor,

05:34.733 --> 05:37.867
the wife and mother who vanished
in the Crumlin area of Dublin...

05:37.867 --> 05:39.667
Aliens, I bet.

05:39.667 --> 05:40.667
Sorry?

05:40.667 --> 05:42.433
It's an abduction, isn't it?

05:42.433 --> 05:43.633
Aliens.

05:44.733 --> 05:47.067
It's just a theory.
I could be wrong.

05:47.733 --> 05:50.167
I'm Glenn.
You a friend of Harry's?

05:50.167 --> 05:52.567
-From the college, yes.
-Oh.

05:53.667 --> 05:56.067
I always thought about going
to college back in Wales,

05:56.067 --> 05:59.200
but, uh, in the end,
decided it wasn't for me.

05:59.200 --> 06:00.600
It's not for everyone.

06:01.533 --> 06:03.367
I've got one of the highest IQs

06:03.367 --> 06:06.067
if not  the highest IQ
in the world.

06:06.800 --> 06:08.533
Never been tested or nothing,

06:08.533 --> 06:12.067
but I can answer pretty much all
the questions on "Pointless."

06:12.067 --> 06:13.867
Right.

06:13.867 --> 06:15.233
So, uh, what do you do?

06:15.233 --> 06:17.100
Oh, bit of this, bit of that.

06:17.667 --> 06:21.567
Work in a phone repair shop
part time.

06:22.533 --> 06:24.767
Carl.

06:26.133 --> 06:28.067
I'm not much of a drinker,
actually.

06:28.067 --> 06:29.533
One can't hurt.

06:29.533 --> 06:31.067
GLENN:
Go on.

06:31.067 --> 06:33.833
[ Mid-tempo music playing
in distance ]

06:41.600 --> 06:44.267
Is that the sound
of our hearts beating?

06:44.267 --> 06:46.600
It's better if you don't talk.

06:48.067 --> 06:50.067
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

06:50.067 --> 06:53.067
[ Sirens wailing in distance ]

06:53.067 --> 06:55.233
[ Indistinct talking on radio ]

07:00.167 --> 07:02.067
[ Engine shuts off ]

07:09.533 --> 07:12.067
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

07:19.067 --> 07:20.467
Sir.

07:23.600 --> 07:25.067
CHARLIE:
What have we got, Vics?

07:25.733 --> 07:28.900
No ID. Been here a day.
Two at the most.

07:34.400 --> 07:36.867
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

07:39.067 --> 07:41.400
Furniture's been moved.
Marks on the floor.

07:46.633 --> 07:49.200
Whoever did this
wanted to direct our eye.

07:52.067 --> 07:54.733
[ Indistinct conversations,
bell rings ]

07:54.733 --> 07:59.400
When Catherine returns
from Thrushcross Grange,

07:59.400 --> 08:04.200
she is a very different
Catherine to the one who left.

08:04.200 --> 08:08.867
Heathcliff, who has pined
for his soul mate,

08:08.867 --> 08:13.067
is unnerved by this new and --

08:13.067 --> 08:14.233
Uh, Fergus...

08:14.800 --> 08:16.067
...what are you doing?

08:16.067 --> 08:18.633
Just cutting out
the middle man, sir.

08:18.633 --> 08:20.867
I was gonna take myself
to Mr. Ellis' office,

08:20.867 --> 08:22.833
'cause that's where
you're gonna be sending me

08:22.833 --> 08:24.733
in about 30 seconds.

08:24.733 --> 08:25.833
Look, I'll be honest.

08:25.833 --> 08:27.467
It's way too hot in here,

08:27.467 --> 08:29.067
and I haven't heard
a word you've said

08:29.067 --> 08:31.767
about Pride and thingy
all lesson.

08:31.767 --> 08:33.367
It's "Wuthering Heights."

08:33.367 --> 08:35.600
FERGUS: That's exactly my point!
Look.

08:35.600 --> 08:38.267
[ Sighs ] You're gonna
tell me to sit down.

08:38.267 --> 08:41.333
I'm going to politely decline,

08:41.333 --> 08:43.667
and you're gonna tell me
that I'm too cocksure.

08:43.667 --> 08:47.233
So I'll say,
"I  am very sure of my cock, sir.

08:47.233 --> 08:48.533
Thanks for noticing."

08:48.533 --> 08:50.233
You'll tell me
to stop being so filthy.

08:50.233 --> 08:52.333
I'll say, "That's not
what your wife said last night,"

08:52.333 --> 08:55.367
and that'll make the tick
in your eye start up -- like so.

08:55.367 --> 08:59.167
So I'll make a make a joke about
you giving me the wink, eh,

08:59.167 --> 09:01.267
say, "I'm not really into you
like that, sir.

09:01.267 --> 09:02.733
Can we just be friends?"

09:02.733 --> 09:05.767
And you'll tell me to get out
of your class,

09:05.767 --> 09:07.633
so...I will.

09:07.633 --> 09:09.400
I just thought I'd save us both
some time

09:09.400 --> 09:11.567
and unnecessary aggravation.

09:11.567 --> 09:12.867
All right?

09:12.867 --> 09:14.067
Okay, fella.

09:14.067 --> 09:16.533
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

09:16.533 --> 09:18.067
[ Students murmuring ]

09:18.067 --> 09:20.867
-[ Clears throat ]
-[ Door closes ]

09:20.867 --> 09:23.067
[ Music continues ]

09:26.400 --> 09:28.833
[ Birds crying ]

09:30.433 --> 09:33.200
