I'm running really late.

17:15.133 --> 17:17.533
Edmund Porter --
Do you remember him?

17:17.533 --> 17:19.533
Well, I'd be surprised
if you did.

17:19.533 --> 17:21.600
He was a contemporary
of Shakespeare and Marlowe,

17:21.600 --> 17:25.067
friend of the latter, um,
always lived in their shadow.

17:25.067 --> 17:27.267
Terrific.
Love, have you seen my phone?

17:27.267 --> 17:29.400
Oh, yeah.
It's by the toaster here.

17:29.400 --> 17:31.400
This can't be a coincidence.

17:31.400 --> 17:33.233
Brilliant. Thanks.
What can't?

17:33.233 --> 17:36.167
"Calabras,"
his best-known work --

17:36.167 --> 17:38.200
although that's not saying much.

17:38.200 --> 17:43.167
In Act 2, Scene 3,
the painter kills his father.

17:43.167 --> 17:46.133
Now, I'm not saying that yours
is the son or a painter --

17:46.133 --> 17:50.067
although it might be --
but the way the body was lying,

17:50.067 --> 17:52.733
with the head bashed in
with the candles all around...

17:52.733 --> 17:55.433
Are you talking about --
Did you read my casebook?

17:55.433 --> 17:57.233
Well, I couldn't sleep
last night, so I --

17:57.233 --> 17:58.533
Harry, you can't do that!

17:58.533 --> 18:00.067
Don't you raise your voice
at me.

18:00.067 --> 18:01.333
