with one of these.

20:28.333 --> 20:30.133
I was crapping myself
coming over here.

20:30.133 --> 20:31.167
Give it over, then.

20:32.267 --> 20:33.800
What's your Charlie gonna say,
eh?

20:33.800 --> 20:35.600
Glenn.

20:35.600 --> 20:37.400
All right.
All right.

20:37.400 --> 20:39.333
I've said my piece.

20:39.333 --> 20:41.000
[ Exhales deeply ]

20:41.000 --> 20:44.533
It's fully charged,
so be careful, okay?

20:44.533 --> 20:46.433
Wrist strap's a safety feature.

20:46.433 --> 20:48.367
It's got to be on your wrist
for it to work.

20:48.367 --> 20:50.233
Someone tries to grab it
off you,

20:50.233 --> 20:52.733
this pin will pop out,
and it'll be useless.

20:52.800 --> 20:56.033
Just means someone can't
turn around and zap you.

20:56.800 --> 20:59.400
You press this and this and...

20:59.400 --> 21:01.067
[ Crackling ]

21:02.067 --> 21:04.067
This type,
you've got to touch it

21:04.067 --> 21:05.533
to the person
who's attacking you.

21:05.533 --> 21:06.867
You push it up against 'em

21:06.867 --> 21:09.167
and press the buttons
like I showed you.

21:09.167 --> 21:11.300
It won't...kill them, though,
will it?

21:12.067 --> 21:14.233
I don't know.
It's not my field.

21:14.233 --> 21:16.067
I just know a bloke
who knows a bloke.

21:16.667 --> 21:19.367
It's got different settings,
though -- low, medium...

21:19.367 --> 21:21.067
Hi!
[ Chuckles ]

21:21.067 --> 21:22.800
What's that you've got, Harry?
A book, is it?

21:22.800 --> 21:24.467
No, Glenn.
It's a flamingo.

21:24.467 --> 21:26.533
[ Chuckles ]
Flamingo.

21:26.533 --> 21:29.267
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]
I can see it's a book.

21:29.267 --> 21:31.067
Looks old.
What's it about?

21:31.067 --> 21:33.133
It's about a painter

21:33.133 --> 21:36.067
who kills an actor,
his own wife, and his father.

21:36.067 --> 21:39.067
Huh. Sounds like my place
at Christmas.

21:39.067 --> 21:41.400
What's he do that for, then,
murder all those people?

21:41.400 --> 21:43.167
Not right in the head, I'd say.

21:43.167 --> 21:46.067
His wife was having an affair
with the actor and the father.

21:46.067 --> 21:48.767
His own father?
Dirty old bastard.

21:48.767 --> 21:52.600
First he hangs the actor,
makes it look like suicide.

21:52.600 --> 21:56.067
Then he drowns the wife
in the bathtub,

21:56.067 --> 21:59.267
chops her up,
and bakes her into a pie --

21:59.267 --> 22:01.533
straight out
of "Titus Andronicus."

22:01.533 --> 22:03.900
And then he bashes
his father's brains in.

22:05.600 --> 22:08.400
If I wanted to kill someone,
you know what I'd do?

22:08.400 --> 22:10.067
I'd strangle 'em with a belt

22:10.067 --> 22:12.400
and put bondage porn
on their computer,

22:12.400 --> 22:15.867
make it look like
that auto-exotic fixation.

22:16.433 --> 22:17.767
What happens in the end, then?

22:17.767 --> 22:19.767
Pigs get him, do they?
FBI swoop in?

22:19.767 --> 22:22.200
This was written 430 years ago,
Glenn.

22:22.200 --> 22:23.300
No FBI.

22:25.133 --> 22:28.233
Actually, he does get away
with it.

22:28.233 --> 22:31.133
The father is due
to be remarried.

22:31.133 --> 22:34.800
The painter steals away
the father's bride,

22:34.800 --> 22:38.300
boards a boat to Bohemia,
never to be seen again.

22:39.433 --> 22:41.433
They were stealing women away
back then.

22:41.433 --> 22:43.367
They're still doing it today.

22:43.367 --> 22:45.067
Should be a law against it,
I say.

22:45.067 --> 22:47.367
Well, there is a law against it.
It --

22:47.367 --> 22:49.267
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

22:49.267 --> 22:51.267
Are you talking about the woman
on the news?

22:51.833 --> 22:54.067
Kayleigh Connor.
Yeah.

22:54.067 --> 22:56.067
Maybe she's on a slow boat
to Bohemia.

22:57.833 --> 23:00.400
Why didn't  I see this?

23:00.400 --> 23:01.433
Oh, my God.

23:05.667 --> 23:08.067
You bloody beauty, Glenn.

23:08.067 --> 23:09.500
Mm. Mm!

23:11.733 --> 23:14.400
-[ Doorbell rings ]
-LOLA: I'll get it.

23:15.067 --> 23:16.633
Someone else joining us,
Charlie?

23:16.633 --> 23:18.133
Didn't invite anyone else.

23:18.133 --> 23:19.433
[ Door closes ]

23:19.433 --> 23:20.467
Ah. Mother.

23:20.467 --> 23:22.133
We have to talk.
It's urgent.

23:22.133 --> 23:24.467
-Charlie.
-This is your mother?

23:25.733 --> 23:28.067
Ray Tiernan.
Heard a lot about you.

23:28.067 --> 23:30.333
Oh. Well, I've heard
absolutely nothing about you.

23:30.333 --> 23:32.067
Don't even know who you are.
Sorry.

23:32.067 --> 23:34.567
-Charlie, we've got to talk now.
-Charlie.

23:34.567 --> 23:36.733
Why does she keep saying
your name?

23:36.733 --> 23:38.067
Is she having a stroke
or something?

23:38.067 --> 23:39.833
Now is not a good time.
We have guests.

23:39.833 --> 23:42.567
Oh. Really? So you've solved
all the crime, then.

23:42.567 --> 23:45.133
Oh. Well, that's a relief.
[ Laughs ]

23:45.133 --> 23:46.767
Vivian Mitchell-Tiernan.

23:46.767 --> 23:48.833
Uh, no idea what you just said.

23:48.833 --> 23:50.833
My name.
I'm assistant commissioner.

23:50.833 --> 23:53.067
Please hold that thought.
Um...

23:53.067 --> 23:54.833
Sorry.

23:54.833 --> 23:58.233
You can't continue to do this.
Can you not just be normal?

23:58.233 --> 24:00.067
Would you just shut up?

24:00.533 --> 24:02.067
The play that I'm
telling you about...

24:02.067 --> 24:03.200
[ Sighs ]

24:03.200 --> 24:05.133
...the killer
doesn't get punished.

24:05.133 --> 24:06.867
He gets rewarded.

24:06.867 --> 24:08.333
The father was due
to be married,

24:08.333 --> 24:11.367
and he gets the father's bride,
Delilah.

24:11.367 --> 24:14.333
She was an actress,
star of the show.

24:14.333 --> 24:17.167
Look, whoever bashed in
Leonard Walsh's head

24:17.167 --> 24:19.067
kidnapped Kayleigh Connor.

24:19.067 --> 24:21.567
-She's his Delilah.
-This has to stop!

24:21.567 --> 24:24.133
Kayleigh Connor's not a star.
She works in the bloody chipper.

24:24.133 --> 24:27.067
But on the news, her husband
said she was an actress.

24:27.067 --> 24:28.333
Well, she's not.

24:28.333 --> 24:29.733
She's part of some crappy
little am-dram group

24:29.733 --> 24:31.067
who've never even put on
a performance.

24:31.067 --> 24:32.333
There's no connection!

24:32.333 --> 24:33.833
I am trying to tell you
the connection.

24:34.533 --> 24:37.200
The -- The killer
has been twisting the play

24:37.200 --> 24:40.067
to suit his own sick desires.

24:40.067 --> 24:41.467
He knew her.

24:41.467 --> 24:43.733
He coveted her.

24:43.733 --> 24:45.867
And how do we covet?

24:45.867 --> 24:48.233
Do we seek things out to covet?

24:48.233 --> 24:51.067
That's a-a quote, right?
From, uh, Cicero or someone.

24:51.067 --> 24:53.167
Hannibal Lecter,
"Silence of the Lambs."

24:53.167 --> 24:55.200
-But don't you see?
-No, I don't!

24:55.200 --> 24:57.333
You have no experience
investigating a crime.

24:57.333 --> 24:59.633
You're just seeing
what you want to see.

25:00.200 --> 25:02.833
No.
But...the candles.

25:02.833 --> 25:05.333
There was no electricity
in the house -- simple as that.

25:05.333 --> 25:07.333
You can't be that obtuse.
I gave birth to you.

25:07.333 --> 25:08.800
Oh.
[ Exhales sharply ]

25:08.800 --> 25:11.067
The first murder in the play
was a hanged man

25:11.067 --> 25:12.400
made to look like a suicide.

25:12.400 --> 25:15.367
And beside his body --
a peacock feather.

25:15.367 --> 25:17.267
Surely you can look
into those things.

25:17.267 --> 25:19.200
Yeah.
I can check the feather log.

25:19.767 --> 25:21.400
It's just like talking
to your father.

25:22.067 --> 25:24.533
-Don't say that.
-I just want to help you.

25:24.533 --> 25:26.067
-Goodbye, Harry.
-No.

25:26.067 --> 25:28.067
-You --
-Goodbye, Harry.

25:28.067 --> 25:29.833
I just --

25:29.833 --> 25:31.400
[ Exhales deeply ]

25:31.400 --> 25:33.200
[ Children shouting ]

25:33.200 --> 25:35.200
Glenn, it's Harry.

25:35.200 --> 25:37.833
I need you to get an address
for Kayleigh Connor's house.

25:37.833 --> 25:39.567
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

25:39.567 --> 25:41.333
[ Indistinct conversations ]

25:41.333 --> 25:43.567
Glenn, I've got to
call you back.

25:47.067 --> 25:48.600
GIRL:
Fergus! Fergus, look at me!

25:48.600 --> 25:50.067
FERGUS: Whoa, whoa, whoa,
little stinker.

25:50.067 --> 25:51.800
What you doing up there?
Geez!

25:51.800 --> 25:53.733
What you trying to do?
Give me a heart attack?

25:53.733 --> 25:54.833
Down you get.

25:54.833 --> 25:56.567
Wah!

25:56.567 --> 25:59.067
You know not to get so high up
without your big brother around,

25:59.067 --> 26:00.267
hey, smelly belly?

26:00.267 --> 26:01.667
Come on.
Let's go.

26:01.667 --> 26:03.700
[ Music continues ]

26:04.467 --> 26:06.067
Only after bath time, though.

26:06.067 --> 26:08.600
-Aww!
-See? Oh, little stinker.

26:08.600 --> 26:10.600
You know it's always bath time
first.

26:10.600 --> 26:13.800
Bath time, then TV, then
some snacks if we're lucky, eh?

26:13.800 --> 26:15.067
Yeah.

26:15.067 --> 26:16.267
Do we have any popcorn?

26:16.267 --> 26:18.200
FERGUS: Hmm.
Do we have any popcorn?

26:18.200 --> 26:20.200
You know,
I think your older brother

26:20.200 --> 26:23.067
might find some popcorn for you
in the cupboard there.

26:23.067 --> 26:25.067
What's your favorite kind?
Sweet and salty, eh?

26:25.067 --> 26:26.267
GIRL:
Yeah. Mm-mmm.

26:26.267 --> 26:29.433
[ Latch clicks, door opens ]

26:29.433 --> 26:32.333
[ Keyboard clicking,
telephone ringing ]

26:32.333 --> 26:35.067
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

26:38.167 --> 26:40.267
Boss, we've got something.

26:40.267 --> 26:43.067
Damian Murphy is one of the kids
Leonard Walsh abused

26:43.067 --> 26:44.667
12 years ago.

26:44.667 --> 26:46.867
He works at a homeless shelter
on Pearse Street now.

26:46.867 --> 26:50.700
He's got a record --
assault, always older men.

26:51.733 --> 26:53.233
Bloody brilliant, Jord.

26:53.233 --> 26:55.667
-Take Vicky. Go pick him up.
-Boss.

26:55.667 --> 26:57.200
[ Exhales deeply ]

26:57.200 --> 27:00.067
[ Doorbell rings ]

27:01.867 --> 27:02.900
Mr. Connor.

27:03.767 --> 27:06.267
Vivian Mitchell-Tiernan,
assistant commissioner.

27:06.267 --> 27:08.133
Oh. Right.

27:08.133 --> 27:10.567
Just a courtesy call,
see how you're holding up.

27:11.567 --> 27:13.067
Yeah.

27:16.433 --> 27:18.333
KEVIN: Family liaison officer
was just here.

27:18.333 --> 27:20.767
-She didn't say you were coming.
-Oh, came on a whim.

27:21.600 --> 27:24.267
Heard you on the news.
It moved me.

27:24.267 --> 27:27.300
I wanted to reassure you --
We will find Kayleigh.

27:28.200 --> 27:29.767
Thank you.

27:30.467 --> 27:32.700
You don't know how good
that is to hear.

27:33.600 --> 27:36.567
Leslie, the liaison officer,

27:36.567 --> 27:39.600
said you lot don't like
making promises you can't keep.

27:39.600 --> 27:42.200
Oh, this is one we will keep.
Trust me.

27:43.267 --> 27:46.133
Tell me about Kayleigh.
She was an actress?

27:46.133 --> 27:47.567
Yeah.

27:47.567 --> 27:49.767
It's a bit of an exaggeration.

27:49.767 --> 27:52.467
It's her dream.
Always has been.

27:53.067 --> 27:57.633
She joined an am-dram group,
but it folded before it started.

27:57.633 --> 27:59.833
The theater they hired
was shut down by the bank,

27:59.833 --> 28:03.133
and only four of them
turned up -- Kayleigh,

28:03.133 --> 28:06.667
Gwen -- she's 80-odd
and deaf as a tree --

28:06.667 --> 28:10.233
and Maurice and Bernie,
a gay couple who started it.

28:10.233 --> 28:11.800
I heard they immigrated
to Canada.

28:11.800 --> 28:12.833
Emigrated.

28:13.767 --> 28:16.067
"Emigrated" when they go,
"immigrated" when they come.

28:18.067 --> 28:20.767
It's -- It's not important.

28:21.600 --> 28:24.567
What was the name
of that theater?

28:24.567 --> 28:26.600
-Uh, just out of interest.
-[ Doorbell rings ]

28:26.600 --> 28:27.867
Oh, that must be Leslie.

28:27.867 --> 28:29.133
She just nipped out
for some bread.

28:29.133 --> 28:30.367
Leslie?

28:30.367 --> 28:32.467
Yeah.
The family liaison officer?

28:33.733 --> 28:35.833
Probably not a good idea
if she sees me here.

28:35.833 --> 28:39.333
It's a little bit against
protocol, me coming like this.

28:39.333 --> 28:41.067
You -- Do you have a back door?

28:41.533 --> 28:44.067
-Yeah.
-Oh. Thank you.

28:46.400 --> 28:48.400
[ Birds chirping ]

28:49.433 --> 28:52.400
Where did you say
that am-dram group used to meet?

28:52.400 --> 28:53.767
Might be important.
You never know.

28:53.767 --> 28:56.133
Oh.
The Gantry in Dún Laoghaire.

28:56.133 --> 28:57.433
Righto.

28:57.433 --> 28:59.167
Chin up, Mr. Connor.

28:59.167 --> 29:01.467
We'll get her back
lickety-split.

29:01.467 --> 29:03.067
[ Doorbell rings ]

29:03.067 --> 29:05.067
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

29:06.667 --> 29:08.800
[ Birds crying ]

29:18.067 --> 29:20.433
[ Music continues ]

29:32.067 --> 29:33.200
[ Hinges creaking ]

29:33.200 --> 29:36.067
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

30:06.767 --> 30:08.867
[ Music continues ]

30:35.200 --> 30:37.900
-[ Metal squeaks ]
-[ Gasps ] Is someone here?

30:40.833 --> 30:43.033
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

30:49.033 --> 30:50.367
-MAN: Who are you?!
-[ Screams ]

30:50.367 --> 30:51.733
-[ Electricity crackling ]
-Aah!

30:51.733 --> 30:53.200
-[ Groans ]
-[ Gasps ]

30:53.200 --> 30:54.767
[ Gasping ]

30:57.067 --> 30:59.567
-[ Inhales sharply ]
-[ Gasps ]

30:59.567 --> 31:01.800
What the bloody hell was that?!

31:01.800 --> 31:03.333
Is this your theater?

31:03.333 --> 31:05.067
Feck off out of it,
you mad bitch.

31:05.067 --> 31:07.533
-[ Electricity crackling ]
-Hey. Okay. Okay.

31:07.533 --> 31:09.733
Yes, this is my theater.

31:09.733 --> 31:14.267
Or was until the bank
foreclosed.

31:14.267 --> 31:16.600
Do you know
who Kayleigh Connor is?

31:16.600 --> 31:18.067
No.
Should I?

31:18.067 --> 31:20.067
She was part
of an am-dram group.

31:20.067 --> 31:21.667
-They used to rehearse here.
-Oh.

31:21.667 --> 31:24.067
I remember them.
They only came here a few times.

31:24.067 --> 31:25.400
I never even met them.

31:25.400 --> 31:28.133
Lloyd, the stage manager,
used to let them in.

31:28.133 --> 31:30.367
-Lloyd? Can I talk to him?
-No.

31:30.367 --> 31:33.600
Took the closure far worse
than the rest of us.

31:34.667 --> 31:35.767
Hung himself.

31:35.767 --> 31:38.067
-Hanged.
-Huh?

31:38.067 --> 31:40.067
Pictures are hung,
people hanged.

31:40.067 --> 31:42.767
Anyway,
he was the stage manager?

31:42.767 --> 31:44.067
Not an actor?

31:44.067 --> 31:45.467
Primarily, he was an actor

31:45.467 --> 31:48.800
but he was just
a better stage manager.

31:50.367 --> 31:52.067
Would anyone else have met them?

31:52.067 --> 31:55.433
Not really. I mean,
Colin would've been here.

31:55.433 --> 31:56.867
He's my, uh, set designer

31:56.867 --> 31:59.333
who was working on, uh,
our next production.

31:59.333 --> 32:00.367
Colin who?

32:01.067 --> 32:03.600
Fountain.
Colin Fountain.

32:03.600 --> 32:04.767
Oh!

32:04.767 --> 32:06.200
Lovely bloke.

32:07.067 --> 32:08.633
Loved baking.

32:08.633 --> 32:11.867
Always bringing in little pies
and samosas.

32:11.867 --> 32:13.167
[ Chuckles ]

32:13.167 --> 32:16.867
All we needed
was a few more weeks.

32:16.867 --> 32:19.167
The next production
would've been a game changer.

32:19.167 --> 32:20.833
What was it called?

32:20.833 --> 32:24.767
-"Calabras" by Edmund Porter.
-[ Dramatic music plays ]

32:24.767 --> 32:27.367
You've probably never heard
of it.

32:28.567 --> 32:30.600
Where does Colin live?

32:31.400 --> 32:34.067
-[ Cellphone ringing ]
-Ugh.

32:34.067 --> 32:35.533
Now is not a good time.

32:35.533 --> 32:39.333
I know who killed Leonard Walsh
and has Kayleigh Connor.

32:39.333 --> 32:41.533
-Get a pen. It's someone who --
-Harry, it's over.

32:41.533 --> 32:43.067
We've got the person
who killed Leonard Walsh.

32:43.067 --> 32:46.067
It was nothing to do
with the play or Kayleigh.

32:46.067 --> 32:47.433
It was something from his past.

32:47.433 --> 32:48.833
No! No.
That's not right.

32:48.833 --> 32:51.167
Well, it is,
so now you can drop it, yeah?

32:51.167 --> 32:53.067
Go and get on
with your retirement.

32:53.067 --> 32:56.233
Take up knitting, maybe think
about a cruise or buy a cat.

32:57.067 --> 32:59.067
Find old-lady stuff to do.

32:59.067 --> 33:01.367
Cat.
[ Exhales sharply ]

33:01.433 --> 33:03.433
[ Door opens ]

33:03.433 --> 33:06.467
[ Telephone ringing,
siren wailing in distance ]

33:10.600 --> 33:12.900
[ Birds chirping, dog barking ]

33:33.567 --> 33:36.200
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

33:38.167 --> 33:40.367
[ Sighs ]

33:45.067 --> 33:47.233
[ Birds crying ]

33:54.667 --> 33:56.700
[ Music continues ]

33:58.433 --> 34:00.867
[ Birds chirping, dog barking ]

34:27.067 --> 34:29.067
Libby's swimming's coming along.

34:30.233 --> 34:32.467
She can almost put her face
under.

34:34.767 --> 34:38.067
Yeah. Dad said he might come up
and see you soon.

34:38.633 --> 34:41.233
I wouldn't get your hopes up,
though.

34:41.233 --> 34:43.867
You know what he's like.

34:43.867 --> 34:46.467
I'll let you know
if he  is coming, though,

34:46.467 --> 34:49.100
give you time to do your hair
and stuff.

34:50.367 --> 34:52.300
Your grandmother?

34:53.433 --> 34:54.500
Yeah.

34:55.800 --> 34:57.467
Nice of you
to bring her flowers.

34:58.467 --> 35:00.667
Carnations.
They were her favorite.

35:00.667 --> 35:01.767
No, they weren't.

35:03.133 --> 35:05.067
Carnations aren't
anyone's favorites.

35:05.067 --> 35:07.500
Grandmothers just say that
because they don't cost so much.

35:08.267 --> 35:11.900
She also told me not to talk
to strange women, so...

35:13.800 --> 35:18.067
Unusual for a boy
to visit his dead granny.

35:18.733 --> 35:20.767
Close, were you?

35:20.767 --> 35:23.067
Yeah.
Yeah, we were.

35:23.067 --> 35:26.600
I wonder what she'd think about
you mugging old ladies, then.

35:27.733 --> 35:29.533
What are you on about?

35:29.533 --> 35:32.200
-Haven't gone anywhere near you.
-Oh, not today.

35:32.200 --> 35:36.067
But last week in Dún Laoghaire,
you shoved me.

35:36.067 --> 35:38.200
You stole my wallet.

35:38.200 --> 35:42.333
I wonder what little old dead
Granny would say about that.

35:42.333 --> 35:45.067
Nah. You must have me mixed up
with someone else.

35:45.067 --> 35:47.633
Oh.
Well, we both know I don't.

35:48.633 --> 35:51.067
Well, if I did...

35:51.067 --> 35:53.467
it'd be pretty stupid,
you coming here.

35:54.200 --> 35:55.867
I mean, look around.

35:56.867 --> 36:00.600
We're all alone, hey?

36:00.600 --> 36:02.267
So why don't you piss off, yeah?

36:02.267 --> 36:03.800
[ Electricity crackling ]

36:03.800 --> 36:06.067
-Aah!
-That's just the low level.

36:06.067 --> 36:09.167
-I could turn it up if you like.
-[ Grunts, coughs ]

36:09.167 --> 36:11.567
Yeah. Yeah -- I mean no.
Don't.

36:11.567 --> 36:13.333
Please.

36:13.333 --> 36:16.400
I remember, all right?
[ Breathing heavily ]

36:16.400 --> 36:19.133
What the hell was that?!
That really hurt.

36:19.133 --> 36:21.467
-Good.
-What do you want from me?

36:21.467 --> 36:23.467
I want to figure you out.

36:23.467 --> 36:25.233
You're a little shithead,

36:25.233 --> 36:27.333
but I've seen how you look after
your sister.

36:28.233 --> 36:31.800
And you tend
your grandmother's grave.

36:31.800 --> 36:34.067
These two sides of you
don't go together.

36:34.067 --> 36:35.467
Maybe I don't want to be
figured out.

36:35.467 --> 36:37.300
What did you do with my money?

36:37.867 --> 36:39.067
Hookers and coke.

36:39.733 --> 36:42.067
There -- There was only
30 euros.

36:42.067 --> 36:44.167
They weren't very good hookers
and coke.

36:44.733 --> 36:48.167
That wallet has sentimental
value, you shithead.

36:48.167 --> 36:50.300
My son's a guard.

36:51.067 --> 36:54.433
I am going to keep an eye
on you, Mr. Reid.

36:54.433 --> 36:59.533
You mug anyone else, and I am
going to give him all your info.

36:59.533 --> 37:00.667
Got it?

37:02.567 --> 37:05.067
[ Sighs ]

37:05.067 --> 37:06.833
Bollocks.

37:06.833 --> 37:08.667
[ Siren wails ]

37:10.633 --> 37:12.567
[ Telephone ringing ]

37:12.567 --> 37:16.067
His alibi checked out.
Ran 'cause he was dealing pills.

37:16.067 --> 37:18.167
Gave him a caution.
Sent him on his way.

37:18.167 --> 37:21.267
Never mind.
Tomorrow's another day.

37:21.267 --> 37:23.567
Ray, where are we with Kayleigh?

37:23.567 --> 37:24.867
Nowhere.

37:25.433 --> 37:27.233
It's like she vanished
off the face of the earth.

37:27.233 --> 37:29.733
No chance her abduction
could be connected

37:29.733 --> 37:31.467
to Leonard Walsh's murder,
is there?

37:31.467 --> 37:33.600
Uh, never mind.

37:33.600 --> 37:36.633
Just something my mam --
someone said.

37:36.633 --> 37:38.233
Forget it.

37:38.233 --> 37:40.433
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

37:41.767 --> 37:43.800
[ Birds chirping ]

37:43.800 --> 37:45.633
CHARLIE:
I was so sure we had him.

37:46.867 --> 37:47.900
Come here.

37:49.200 --> 37:51.133
Look.
You've been here before.

37:51.133 --> 37:53.867
You'll find who it is.
You know that.

37:53.867 --> 37:56.400
Just as long as Harry doesn't
find out we had the wrong man.

37:56.400 --> 37:59.133
I'll never hear
the bloody end of it.

37:59.133 --> 38:01.867
[ Exhales deeply ]

38:01.867 --> 38:04.800
-[ Cellphone clicking, chimes ]
-I can feel those knots.

38:06.467 --> 38:08.900
[ Cellphone chimes ]

38:21.067 --> 38:23.067
[ Music continues ]

38:25.133 --> 38:27.067
[ Gasps ] What the bloody hell
are you doing here?

38:27.067 --> 38:28.233
Sod off!
Go!

38:28.233 --> 38:30.067
You said it had
sentimental value, okay?

38:30.067 --> 38:32.233
I just...

38:33.067 --> 38:35.067
Most of the money's there.

38:35.067 --> 38:37.867
Half. Okay.
Almost half.

38:37.867 --> 38:39.767
I'll never come here again.

38:39.767 --> 38:41.833
How do you know where I live?

38:41.833 --> 38:43.200
Driving license.

38:43.200 --> 38:44.567
Ah.
Smart, huh?

38:47.400 --> 38:50.100
How would you like to earn
some of that money back?

38:52.367 --> 38:54.233
Okay.

38:54.233 --> 38:56.233
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

38:56.233 --> 38:58.900
[ Birds chirping, squawking ]

39:00.867 --> 39:02.633
FERGUS:
Whose house is that?

39:03.600 --> 39:07.067
My son the guard is looking for
a killer and a kidnapper --

39:07.067 --> 39:09.167
the same person who's done both.

39:09.167 --> 39:11.100
Okay.
And?

39:12.567 --> 39:14.067
Wait.

39:14.067 --> 39:15.767
Are you saying the killer's
over there?

39:15.767 --> 39:17.167
Well, I'm 90% sure.

39:17.167 --> 39:18.600
So call your son!

39:18.600 --> 39:22.200
Okay, 75%.
But I have to be certain.

39:22.200 --> 39:24.200
[ Sighs ]

39:24.200 --> 39:26.567
Look.
Here's Charlie's number.

39:26.567 --> 39:28.267
If I'm not out in 15 minutes,

39:28.267 --> 39:30.833
I want you to call him,
tell him what I've done,

39:30.833 --> 39:33.533
and tell him the killer's name
is Colin Fountain.

39:33.533 --> 39:35.067
He worked at the theater

39:35.067 --> 39:38.333
where Kayleigh Connor's
am-dram group rehearsed.

39:38.333 --> 39:41.067
The woman on the news,
the one who's missing?

39:41.067 --> 39:42.400
That's who he's kidnapped?

39:42.400 --> 39:45.067
Well, if I'm right,
she's in there now.

39:46.400 --> 39:47.733
You  will call him, won't you?

39:47.733 --> 39:49.067
I ain't calling him.

39:49.067 --> 39:50.667
[ Sighs ]
"I'm  not calling him."

39:50.667 --> 39:52.200
Yeah.
Me neither.

39:52.200 --> 39:54.067
"Hello, Mr. Guard, sir.

39:54.067 --> 39:56.400
You don't know me,
but last week I mugged your ma,

39:56.400 --> 39:58.467
and now she's gone into
a murderer's house,

39:58.467 --> 40:00.067
and she's not come out."

40:00.067 --> 40:02.633
Yeah, that doesn't end well
for anyone.

40:02.633 --> 40:05.000
How do you know
he's not in there?

40:05.000 --> 40:07.267
I'm just gonna knock
on the door, and --

40:07.267 --> 40:10.200
and if he answers, I'll just say
I've got the wrong address.

40:10.200 --> 40:11.633
I'm just a harmless old woman.

40:11.633 --> 40:13.467
You bleedin' well aren't.

40:13.467 --> 40:15.533
[ Door opens ]

40:15.533 --> 40:17.367
Oh.

40:17.367 --> 40:20.033
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

40:22.000 --> 40:23.667
Well, now we know
he's not there.

40:25.267 --> 40:26.300
W-Wait.

40:36.000 --> 40:38.033
[ Music continues ]

40:39.133 --> 40:41.233
[ Door opens ]

41:15.267 --> 41:17.400
[ Music continues ]

41:22.800 --> 41:25.633
[ Latch clicks,
hinges creaking ]

41:35.067 --> 41:37.100
[ Music continues ]

41:48.633 --> 41:50.833
[ Floorboard creaking ]

41:53.667 --> 41:56.067
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

42:06.833 --> 42:09.067
[ Music continues ]

42:13.467 --> 42:15.433
What am I doing?

42:18.067 --> 42:20.067
Nope. Nope.

42:20.067 --> 42:21.367
Nope.

42:22.067 --> 42:24.200
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

42:57.233 --> 42:59.433
Don't tell me.

42:59.433 --> 43:02.167
-Lasagna again.
-[ Whispering ] Kayleigh.

43:03.067 --> 43:05.067
Oh, my God.

43:05.067 --> 43:06.400
Who are you?

43:06.400 --> 43:08.067
It's all right.
I'm here to help you.

43:08.067 --> 43:10.333
Oh, God. You've got to
get me out of here.

43:10.333 --> 43:13.067
Please.
He's bloody nuts!

43:13.067 --> 43:14.267
I'm going to.

43:14.267 --> 43:15.533
Are you hurt?

43:15.533 --> 43:18.067
No.
He -- He hasn't hurt me.

43:18.067 --> 43:19.733
Right. Good.
Well, come on.

43:19.733 --> 43:21.200
We've got to leave
before he gets back.

43:21.200 --> 43:24.267
Oh, yeah. Like it didn't occur
to me to leave.

43:24.267 --> 43:26.467
The key's on a chain
around his neck.

43:26.467 --> 43:28.067
Oh, shit!

43:28.067 --> 43:29.833
I'm gonna have to find tools
or something.

43:29.833 --> 43:32.200
But --
Is anyone else coming?

43:32.200 --> 43:33.667
Have you called the guards?

43:33.667 --> 43:35.200
Don't worry.
I'll be right back.

43:35.200 --> 43:36.600
Look out!

43:36.600 --> 43:38.233
[ Grunting ]

43:38.233 --> 43:40.367
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

43:44.733 --> 43:46.800
[ Groans ]

43:50.333 --> 43:52.333
[ Voice echoing ]
How long have I been here?

43:52.333 --> 43:53.833
KAYLEIGH:
Not long.

43:53.833 --> 43:56.833
About 10 minutes.

43:58.533 --> 43:59.600
Where is he?

43:59.600 --> 44:01.067
[ Door thuds ]

44:01.067 --> 44:04.067
Oh, good.
You're awake.

44:07.133 --> 44:09.067
[ Drill whirs ]

44:09.067 --> 44:11.067
Don't worry, my darling.

44:11.067 --> 44:13.467
This is for her, not you.

44:14.367 --> 44:15.633
I've got questions.

44:15.633 --> 44:17.067
You can ask all the questions
you like.

44:17.067 --> 44:19.133
It's over for you, Colin.

44:19.133 --> 44:20.133
Who are you?

44:20.133 --> 44:21.767
Inspector Wild.

44:21.767 --> 44:25.067
Bit long in the tooth
to be a guard, now, aren't you?

44:25.067 --> 44:26.600
And you sound English.

44:31.200 --> 44:32.467
College employee.

44:33.133 --> 44:35.067
I'm working for the guards.

44:37.067 --> 44:38.500
Nah.

44:41.067 --> 44:43.067
How did you find us?

44:43.067 --> 44:45.867
My son's Inspector Wild.

44:46.400 --> 44:49.400
He's the one in charge
of the Leonard Walsh murder.

44:50.333 --> 44:52.067
I saw his case notes.
I...

44:53.067 --> 44:56.267
...I spotted the similarities
to "Calabras."

44:57.133 --> 44:58.767
He asked me to advise.

44:59.867 --> 45:03.600
Some of what you said is true --
I think...

45:04.567 --> 45:06.333
...but you're still lying.

45:06.333 --> 45:08.367
No. W-We've --
We've entered the theater.

45:08.367 --> 45:11.433
We've already talked
to your old boss.

45:12.733 --> 45:15.300
We know you killed Lloyd,
the stage manager.

45:15.867 --> 45:18.433
Made it look like suicide.

45:18.433 --> 45:20.200
And we know what you did
to your wife.

45:20.767 --> 45:23.767
Did you feed her
to the theater people?

45:25.067 --> 45:27.667
They couldn't get enough
of those samosas.

45:28.467 --> 45:30.567
I actually planned to do
some pasties, too,

45:30.567 --> 45:34.533
but, um...
she wasn't a big woman.

45:34.533 --> 45:35.833
Wait.

45:37.433 --> 45:39.400
What was in those lasagnas?

45:39.400 --> 45:41.067
No.

45:41.067 --> 45:43.267
I ran out of her
long before you came.

45:43.267 --> 45:46.133
They're just Lidl.

45:46.133 --> 45:48.200
We know it all, Colin.

45:50.133 --> 45:53.233
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

45:54.567 --> 45:56.700
Look away, Delilah.

45:58.067 --> 46:00.067
I don't want you to see this.

46:00.067 --> 46:01.667
[ Drill whirring ]

46:01.667 --> 46:03.133
KAYLEIGH:
[ Screams ]

46:03.133 --> 46:04.233
Wait!
Wait.

46:04.233 --> 46:06.867
There's one thing
you've forgotten.

46:06.867 --> 46:08.167
What about the rascal?

46:08.800 --> 46:10.067
The -- The who?

46:10.067 --> 46:11.133
The rascal.

46:11.133 --> 46:13.833
He foils the painter.

46:13.833 --> 46:15.400
There's no rascal in "Calabras."

46:15.400 --> 46:17.567
HARRY: Y-You must have read
the abridged version.

46:17.567 --> 46:19.600
In Porter's preferred text,

46:19.600 --> 46:23.067
the old crone
keeps the painter talking

46:23.067 --> 46:25.900
so that the rascal could come up
behind him and...

46:26.467 --> 46:27.833
And what?

46:27.833 --> 46:29.167
And do this.

46:29.167 --> 46:30.800
HARRY:
[ Gasps ]

46:30.800 --> 46:33.067
-[ Grunts ] Aah!
-[ Drill whirring ]

46:33.067 --> 46:35.367
The band! The band!
It has to be around your wrist!

46:36.533 --> 46:38.633
-[ Electricity crackling ]
-[ Groans ]

46:41.333 --> 46:44.067
[ Siren wailing ]

46:44.067 --> 46:46.067
[ Indistinct conversations ]

46:46.067 --> 46:48.367
[ Engine stops ]

46:48.367 --> 46:50.267
-Kayleigh!
-Oh!

46:50.267 --> 46:52.067
Oh!
Kevin.

46:52.067 --> 46:53.667
Oh!
[ Sobs ]

46:57.067 --> 46:58.533
Ma.

46:58.533 --> 47:00.633
-Are you okay, Ma?
-I'm fine.

47:00.633 --> 47:02.833
Well, in that case, that was
a mad stupid thing to do.

47:02.833 --> 47:06.067
Well, I wouldn't have had to
do it if you'd listened to me.

47:06.600 --> 47:08.600
You're the one who called?

47:08.600 --> 47:11.067
-Who are you exactly?
-My student.

47:11.067 --> 47:12.533
-Your what?
-What?

47:12.533 --> 47:15.067
You told me to find something
to occupy my time.

47:15.067 --> 47:17.833
I'm a teacher.
Fergus needed extra tuition.

47:19.233 --> 47:22.367
You should thank him
for saving your mother's life.

47:24.667 --> 47:25.767
Thanks.

47:25.767 --> 47:27.867
Aw, you're all right, fella.

47:33.333 --> 47:34.833
[ Exhales deeply ]

47:34.833 --> 47:36.600
Extra tuition?

47:36.600 --> 47:38.267
-What are you on about?
-You're a good kid.

47:38.267 --> 47:40.267
You're intelligent
but stupid with it.

47:40.267 --> 47:42.067
To be honest, I didn't think
you'd stick around.

47:42.067 --> 47:43.400
Well, to be honest,
I almost didn't.

47:43.400 --> 47:45.533
Well, you did,
and that's what matters.

47:45.533 --> 47:47.767
So in return,
I'm going to make a man of you.

47:47.767 --> 47:49.367
I already am a man.

47:49.367 --> 47:50.767
No, you're not.

47:50.767 --> 47:52.867
But you will be
when I'm finished.

47:53.367 --> 47:55.633
I've taught for 24 years.

47:55.633 --> 47:57.067
I'm never wrong
about these things.

47:57.067 --> 47:58.567
Must be tough to never be wrong.

47:58.567 --> 48:01.600
Oh, I'm telling you, Fergus.
It's a pissing burden.

48:01.600 --> 48:04.233
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

48:12.133 --> 48:14.167
[ Music continues ]
